		Me.txtHelpTVMDC.Text = "TVMDC" & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "" & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "a. Purpose:  Update the values of the compass variables True (T), Variation (V), Magnetic (M), Deviation (D), and Compass (C) when any one is changed.  " & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "(T, M, and C can be courses, bearings, or headings, consistent within the tool.)  Calculate the value of variation for a selected year based on the data " & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "provided on a chart." & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "" & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "b. Operation: The window is divided into two sections.  The section on the left does the TVMDC calculation.  The section on the right calculates variation " & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "based on chart data." & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "" & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "TVMDC (left section):" & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "As any value is entered or changed, all other appropriate values change on the fly.  Values of V and D do not change automatically; they only change by " & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "manually entering or changing their values.  If T, M,  or C is changed,the other two are updated.  If V or D are changed, the values below or above them " & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "are updated, depending on whether True to Compass (down arrow) or Compass to True (up arrow) is selected." & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "" & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "Values must be entered in whole degrees.  Leading zeros are not needed.  To change a value, the existing value must be deleted or backspaced over.  " & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "Highlighting then typing the new value will not work." & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "" & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "Press the ""Clear"" button to clear all numerical values." & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "" & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "Variation (right section):" & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "Enter the charted variation (limited to 99°59'), year, and annual change.   Enter the year of interest (default is the system year).  As any of these values is " & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "entered or changed, the value of Corrected Variation is updated automatically.  This value can then be used in the TVMDC section if desired." & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "" & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "There are no limits imposed on the years except they are limited to a maximum of four digits.  Because of this and the fact that Corrected Variation is " & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "calculated automatically, as a year is changed the difference in years can be very large, possibly resulting in an unreasonably large value of Corrected " & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "Variation.  Corrected Variations greater than 99° are flagged with a yellow background to warn of this possibility." & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "" & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "c. Accuracy/Resolution:  For TVMDC, outputs are displayed to three figures, with leading zeros added where appropriate.  For Variation, Corrected " & Chr(13) & Chr(10) & "Variation is  rounded to whole degrees." & Chr(13) & Chr(10)
